# Floating card page layout

Use the **Products page** pattern for new full-height dashboard pages with a sticky header and edge-to-edge floating card.

## Source of truth

- **Components**: `@/components/layout/floating-card-page`
- **Class tokens**: `@/lib/layout/floating-card-page`

## Compose like this

```tsx
<FloatingCardPage>
  <FloatingCardPageHeader>
    <FloatingCardPageTitleRow title="…" icon={Icon} actions={…} />
  </FloatingCardPageHeader>
  <FloatingCardPageBody>
    <FloatingCard>{/* filters + scrollable content */}</FloatingCard>
  </FloatingCardPageBody>
</FloatingCardPage>
```

## Spacing rules

- Top inset: `!pt-2.5` on the page shell (`FloatingCardPage`)
- Header → card gap: `!mt-2.5` on body (`FloatingCardPageBody`) — **must match top inset**
- Reset padding with `!px-0 !pb-0` only — **never `!p-0`** (it removes top padding)
- No extra `pb-*` on the sticky header; gap lives on `PageBody` margin

## Card chrome

- `border border-gray-200`, `rounded-t-xl`, light shadow
- `-ml-px relative z-[1]` so the top-left border sits over the sidebar seam
- No horizontal padding on the page body — card is full bleed

## Dashboard shell

- Hide topbar + `overflow-hidden` on the main column for full-height pages (see `dashboard-layout.tsx` for `/products`)
- Viewport height: `h-[calc(100svh-3.5rem)]`

